post_text: After long and careful deliberation, in a proactive effort to protect the health of our students and staff, the Inglewood Unified School District will close our campuses, including the Child Development Center and Adult School, to students beginning on Monday, March 16, 2020, for the next two weeks until further notice. We will begin to provide instruction remotely.
text: After long and careful deliberation, in a proactive effort to protect the health of our students and staff, the Inglewood Unified School District will close our campuses, including the Child Development Center and Adult School, to students beginning on Monday, March 16, 2020, for the next two weeks until further notice. We will begin to provide instruction remotely.

post_text: Frank D. Parent seventh-grader Saraiyah Slack has been selected for this month's Stellar Student Spotlight! She maintains a 3.7 GPA, is a student fundraising leader for the Associated Student Body (ASB), and a student representative on the School Site Council (SSC). Saraiyah would like to ultimately become a computer science entrepreneur. To nominate a stellar IUSD student to be spotlighted email maygan.orr@inglewoodusd.com
